\begin_layout Enumerate
Now treat 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 as unknown with prior 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\sim Gamma(a_{\alpha},b_{\alpha})$
\end_inset

.
 Add an updating step for 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 in the Blocked Gibbs sampler (see page 553 in BDA3).
 Analyze the Galaxy data again using some suitable values for 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

.
 Plot the prior and posterior of 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

.
 Note that BDA3 uses the so called 
\emph on
rate parametrization
\emph default
 of the Gamma density where if 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim Gamma(a_{\alpha},b_{\alpha})$
\end_inset

 then the pdf is of the form
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p(x)=\frac{\beta^{\alpha}}{\Gamma(\alpha)}x^{\alpha-1}e^{-\beta x}.
\]

\end_inset


